fields.name: Kiwi
fields.description: Kiwi is a sweet cat that loves people. She will greet you at the door when you get home, sleep on your lap while you sit on the couch, and follow you from room to room to keep you company. She has beautiful green eyes and short, little legs. She's not a munchkin, but she has a low center of gravity!

fields.name: Daisy
fields.description: Daisy is a sweet old dog that is forever loyal. She's a people person. She'll follow you around and rest her head on your lap. She still has a playful spirit and will do her best to fetch or wrestle.

fields.name: Burnt Toast (BT)
fields.description: Burnt Toast has a fiery personality. She's feisty and loves to chase anything you throw her direction. She was previously an indoor-outdoor cat, and her foster parent says she loves to sleep on the roof! Better keep your eye on her.

fields.name: Dede
fields.description: Dede is a hilarious dog that looks and acts just like her foster parent! She is a great audience for aspiring musicians. She will lie down in front of you as you play guitar, and she might even give you a bark or two when you hit those high notes!

fields.name: Luna
fields.description: Luna is a sweet dog that is always by your side. She loves to snuggle with her stuffed animals, and she is great with kids. Her foster parent describes her as a rambunctious rascal.

fields.name: Maci
fields.description: Maci is a sweet little girl who has been spoiled. Don't expect her to use her doggy bed. She'll end up taking up most of the room on a king-size bed, even though she's so little! She's wearing a cone of shame right now because she just had surgery on her leg, but it doesn't stop her from being the princess that she is!

fields.name: Mochi
fields.description: Mochi is a unique dog. She's a combination of an estimated 24 breeds (and that's no dog #$%@)! She's got a unique bark, too. It's as deep as Kevin Michael Richardson's voice (bass - no pun intended). You'll love her, we guarantee it.

fields.name: Wally
fields.description: Where's Wally? He's probably right inside the door as you're getting home because he's that excited to see you. Named after Wally from the Dilbert comic strip, he's a great partner for a programmer. If you give him some treats, he might give you some advice. Like this bit here: 'Failure is the raw material of success. If I am not failing, it means I am not pushing myself hard enough.'

fields.name: Zelda
fields.description: It's dangerous to go alone! Wait... this cat wasn't named after that Zelda! She was named after Zelda Harris, the American actress. She's a sweet girl who can definitely put on an act when she wants food!

fields.name: Zoli
fields.description: Zoli is definitely a character. He wasn't named after Fazoli's, but he's been known to sneak some pasta and meatballs off of the floor during dinner time. Zoli loves visitors, so stop on by and give him some attention!

fields.name: Kiwi
fields.description: A sweet cat who's already been adopted.

fields.name: Kiwi on her tree
fields.description: A sweet cat who's also been adopted already.

fields.name: Ultra-lazy Kiwi
fields.description: A lazy cat who's been adopted.

fields.name: Chris P. Bacon
fields.description: Adorable, extremely smart (wins at chess every time), and confident, there's nothing stopping Chris. He's house-trained and is also a big fan of Black Sabbath.

fields.name: Rex
fields.description: He's old, but he's learning new, dino-mite tricks every day. If you ask him if he's able to do something, he always says the same thing: "You bet Jurassican." He's ultra-competitive (definitely a saur loser). He loves to ride his bike (see photo). When his tail gets caught in the spokes, he's a mega-saur-ass about it. He also loves to get together with his friends and sing in a tyranno-chorus. At night, you can't escape his dino-snores.

fields.text: I'd love to adopt this cat. I have plenty of space back home to take care of an indoor-outdoor cat. I've got a barn that she can spend the night in, and she can join me out in the fields during the day.

I can definitely find a place in my home for this sweet cat. I can also give her the outdoor time she wants (she can use the doggy door that I've already got installed)! I only have one dog, but my dog is small and has been around cats before. Please consider me for adoption!
This is already my cat, so I might as well apply to adopt her.
Are you kidding me, an actual dinosaur? That's amazing.

I'd love to adopt this cat. I don't have any other pets or kids currently, and I've got plenty of space. I work part-time, so I'll be able to give her lots of attention. I'm happy to stop by any time to discuss this application!
Crikey, mate. This little bugger would love the outback! Don't look any further, you've found her match.
Rex looks like quite a monster. If he likes to wrestle, then I'm your guy. I've taken on bigger, badder lizards in my time.
Kiwi? That's a bird, not a cat! Either way, this cat's a mad cute lass. I'm sure she'd be happy as an office cat at my zoo.
What a pretty cat! I have another cat at home that could really use another senior friend. Please consider me for adoption. I'd love to bring my cat by to introduce them to each other!
I'd love to adopt this sweet girl. I'm not a crazy cat lady, but I have seven other cats that are always looking for more friends. They're all indoor cats, but they've got plenty of space to play.

fields.description: We need a group of volunteers to help us set up outdoor kennels and also serve food during our grand opening!

This weekend, we are upgrading our indoor cat area! We need a group of people to help build PVC pipe structures and mount wooden platforms on the walls. This activity does require some light lifting and stamina. Lunch is provided!

We're looking for a handful of individuals to help grill hot dogs and burgers this Wednesday evening for our monthly hot dog cookout. You'll get extra exposure to the dogs we have here, and you'll be helping place more of them in forever homes!

All of our animals will have an adoption fee of $0 this weekend, and we need volunteers to help us greet and communicate with visitors to the shelter. We will offer breakfast and a training for one hour before the event.
We're upgrading our guinea pig enclosures to hold another 40 guinea pigs! We need a few volunteers to help us install some wood panels and trim. We'll supply the tools and snacks, too!
We would like a group of dog walkers to help us walk all of our dogs this Thursday!
